commit.message:
Thesaurus / Regions / Brexit

Following EUROSTAT guideline (https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/help/faq/brexit):
* change EU27 to EU27_2007
* add EU27_2020
* clarify labels for EU27* and EU28 with years

For catalogue using this in keywords, the following can be used to update existing records:
```sql
UPDATE metadata SET data = replace(data, '>EU27<', '>EU27_2007<') WHERE metadata LIKE '%>EU_27<%';
```

commit.message:
Update WSDL url to https://

The http URL for the wsdl seem to redirect to https now, while the gem
is currently not following that redirect. This causes Savon::HTTPError
errors:

```
HTTP error (302): <HTML><HEAD>

<TITLE>Redirect</TITLE>
...snipped
```

Example call:

```
curl -svo /dev/null "http://ec.europa.eu/taxation_customs/vies/checkVatService.wsdl"
*   Trying 2a01:7080:14:100::666:30:80...
* Connected to ec.europa.eu (2a01:7080:14:100::666:30) port 80 (#0)
> GET /taxation_customs/vies/checkVatService.wsdl HTTP/1.1
> Host: ec.europa.eu
> User-Agent: curl/7.69.1
> Accept: */*
>
* Mark bundle as not supporting multiuse
< HTTP/1.1 302 Found
< Location: https://ec.europa.eu/taxation_customs/vies/checkVatService.wsdl
< Cache-Control: no-cache
< Pragma: no-cache
< Content-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8
< Proxy-Connection: close
< Connection: close
< Content-Length: 738
<
{ [738 bytes data]
* Closing connection 0
```
